Your controller class is currently a Web Controller and not a REST Controller. When you call the `users` endpoint Spring Boot is trying to find a Thymeleaf template named `users.html` under default location `&lt;classpath&gt;/templates`. It is not there because you don&#39;t want to show a page but just a JSON response with all existing users.

**Solution**

To achieve this add the `@ResponseBody` annotation to the endpoint like this:
```
@GetMapping(&quot;/users&quot;)
@ResponseBody
public List&lt;User&gt; getUsers() {
    return service.getUsers();
}
```
Another option would be to implement the REST endpoints in a separate class annotated with `@RestController`.

